snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a size 20 and I find it so difficult to find clothes I'm comfortable in that look really nice or that I feel sexy in. I find that I'll love how something looks online but it just looks stretched out when I try it on (as in the print) and so many plus size clothes are a block colour in a boring style that doesnt do anything for my confidence - and when I do find nice pieces they tend to be less affordable, Ive looked for hours online and bought a tonne of options of which I return 90% of. There needs to be a new affordable range that women can feel sexy and confident in.

Apart from my health, being able to walk into any high street shop and find something I'm comfortable to wear is the main reason I'm working to lose weight.
